element.name: Mossy by moyle, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)
element.description: Follow the path, enjoy the views and the sound of running water.
element.long-description: Additional Waypoints HH15B8N - Mossy N 53째 14.919 W 006째 17.129 Small space at gate with room for one car.
element.encoded-hints: Beware the mossy monster is watching!!

ul.li:
2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by slands
Initially I had put the wrong co-ords into my GPS, and ended up at another "Mossy". Spent a lot of time, and got lots of nettle stings checking all possible places around there. Just as I was about to give up, I double checked the co-ords on my phone, and found that I was 200M away from GZ [:I]
After re-setting my GPS I was off again. This time got to the right spot. Like others my GPS was all over the place at the site - probably not helped by all the wet trees around. After searching for a while decided to check the hint and spoiler...they did not really help much, apart from telling me which side of the track I should be searching on. It was raining heavily at this point, and I was just about to give up when I spotted it...very well hidden indeed.
Note...it is fairly overgrown here now, so the "Mossy" referred to in the hint and spoiler photo is no longer obvious!
TNLNSL
TFTC.
Stephen...

2010-06-10T19:00:00Z : Found it by colmyster
Third cache of the day. Lovely spot. Even spotted a beekeeper attending his bees... Almost didn't find the cache in the end it was well hidden. Thanks for bringing me here...and so close to home...
In: Dinosaur Out: diabetes travel bug

2010-04-25T19:00:00Z : Found it by Murphymoores
Thanks Great spot

2010-04-25T12:54:59Z : Found it by MurphInerney
Super thanks

2010-04-11T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by AbbeyAckbar
DNF! Not to worry, we won't mind having to come back here again [:)] It's a lovely spot. From looking at the cache page, seems our GPSr led us to look on the wrong side of the path.
